Open Source Software Conference (OSSC) OSOL is a one day event, the biggest main linux event at Hungary, celebrating after the world Software Freedom Day at Szeged's Science and IT University. Lots of talks (more then 40), lots of participants, developers, hackers, business groups - lot of fun. See OSOL_Conference_Szeged

The Free Society Conference and Nordic Summit is a cross-cultural meeting place where grass root organisations, companies, academics, cultural workers and hackers come together in a united effort to discuss and liberate all aspects of digital culture. See FSCONS 2011 for details.

This is the continue of the old FSF conference tradition, what is an one day event where we could meet lots of local users, and companies. They have leaved out the earlier year, but now they will do it again, with long, high quality talks. See FSF-OSSC 2011 for details.
OpenRheinRuhr is a new free software trade show with conference and exhibition in the Rhine-Ruhr region. See http://openrheinruhr.de/ for details.

LinuxDay is a small event in Austria near the Swiss, German, and Lichtenstein border. See LinuxDay Dornbirn 2011.
